   (Message) **ROOT CAUSE:**
   The crash originates from the function
   `CWE122_Heap_Based_Buffer_Overflow__char_type_overrun_memcpy_01_bad()` at
   *program.c:42*. The code copies a source string (`SRC_STR`) into
   `structCharVoid->charFirst` using `sizeof(*structCharVoid)` as the copy size.
   `sizeof(*structCharVoid)` evaluates to the total size of the struct, **not**
   the size of the `charFirst` array that actually holds the data. Consequently,
   when the source string is larger than the allocated buffer, the `memcpy`
   overruns the heap block, corrupting adjacent heap metadata. Later, when
